	(447,64,'venue_4_venue_description','<a href=\"http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=277+Broadway,+Somerville,+MA+02145&amp;sll=42.396175,-71.105103&amp;sspn=0.021393,0.039911&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;z=16&amp;iwloc=addr\" target=\"new\">Find us using Google maps</a>\r\n\r\nTo get to the <a href=\"http://teph.org/\">Elizabeth Peabody House</a> by public transport:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>EPH is about a mile NW (on Broadway) from Sullivan Station on the MBTA Orange Line</li>\r\n	<li>EPH is about two miles SE (on Broadway) from Porter/Davis Squares on the MBTA Red LIne</li>\r\n	<li>The #89 bus passes EPH between Sullivan Station and the Clarendon Hill Busway. It also passes Powderhouse Square, just up College Ave from Davis Square.</li>\r\n	<li>The #101 bus passes EPH between Sullivan Station and Malden Center Station.</li>\r\n	<li>See <a href=\"http://www.mbta.com/\">www.mbta.com</a> for more detailed schedules and routes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTo get there from Route 93:\r\nGoing North from Boston, use Exit 29.\r\nGoing South from the North Shore, use Exit 30 (Mystic Ave)\r\nEither way, you then:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Follow signs for Route 28 South</li>\r\n	<li>Turn right at Broadway and McGrath Highway (Near a park, Dunkin Donuts, and two gas stations.)</li>\r\n	<li>EPH is about three blocks up Broadway, on your right.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThere are several municipal parking areas nearby on Broadway. On-street parking without need for a resident permit is available on Broadway, Grant, Wheatland and Fellsway West (unmetered after 6:00p.m.). The Foss Park parking lot is closed at night, but is available for use during the Sunday matinee.'),
